      <para id="id1164859698636"><emphasis effect="bold">EXPLORING THE ISSUES </emphasis>The learner can take informed decisions on social and environmental issues and problems</para>
      <para id="id1164842714530">
        <emphasis effect="italics">This is clear when the learner:</emphasis>
      </para>
      <list id="id1164859749226" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" mark-suffix="3.1">
        <item/>
        <item>identifies social and environmental conflicts in South Africa and compares it with other contexts [identifies the issue];</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1164842697570">3.2 identifies factors that have an influence on selected social and environmental disputes, including those regarding rights; gender; social, economical and political claims within a specific context [factors affecting the issues];</para>
      <list id="id1164859949829" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" mark-suffix="3.3">
        <item>analyses the reason for disputes or conflicts [makes choices];</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1164851773776">3.4 takes informed decisions on various solutions to social and environmental conflicts [makes choices].</para>
